!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

acid /ˈæsɪd/

(acids) 

1. N-MASS An acid is a chemical substance, usually a liquid, which contains hydrogen and can react with other substances to form salts. Some acids burn or dissolve other substances that they come into contact with. 酸 

例： ...citric acid. …柠檬酸。 

2. ADJ An acid substance contains acid. 酸性的 

例： These shrubs must have an acid, lime-free soil. 这些灌木必须要有酸性、无石灰的土壤。 

3. acidity N-UNCOUNT 酸性 [oft N 'of' n] 

例： ...the acidity of rainwater. …雨水的酸性。

</div>

